Name: Getting the day started
Description: Choose a song that would be good to listen to as you get ready for the day. Keep in mind that you’re probably definitely running a lil late.

Name: Therapy
Description: You made it just in time! You start the day off with a couple of clients and you do some really good therapy. Choose a song that mentions emotion(s).

Name: Lunchtime!
Description: You’ve made it to lunchtime, but what will you eat? Will you take your chances with the leftovers in your mini fridge that you are pretty sure you brought sometime last week? Will you ask the lunch robots to deliver you a smoothie and a bagel? Will you hit up your favorite poke place? But wait, there are a couple of slightly squashed Uncrustables in your bag. So much to choose from. Choose a song that mentions food.

Name: Wits' end
Description: You finish your lunch and soon, you find yourself in a series of increasingly infuriating meetings. Someone asks you a particularly troubling question. Someone tells you that the office is somehow suddenly and urgently Out Of Envelopes. Someone asks if the office would consider getting an emotional support parrot. Someone informs you that nobody in the office but them is doing their job and what are you going to do about it? You consider cartoon violence. Choose a song to help talk you down.

Name: Wits' End 2.0
Description: You finish your lunch and soon, you find yourself in a series of increasingly infuriating meetings. Someone asks you a particularly troubling question. Someone tells you that the office is somehow suddenly and urgently Out Of Envelopes. Someone asks if the office would consider getting an emotional support parrot. Someone informs you that nobody in the office but them is doing their job and what are you going to do about it? You consider cartoon violence. Choose a song to help talk you down.

Name: Hiding
Description: You hole up in your office and put the do not disturb sign on your door. You’re finally going to get some stuff done. You open up the research proposal that’s been sitting in your inbox for too long and start to review it. It was written by a tenured (male) professor, so absolutely no proofreading was involved. You take a couple of seconds to ponder on the machine of academia, patriarchy, and capitalism. You press ahead. Choose a song with a title that is a complete sentence (subj, obj, verb)

Name: Date night
Description: You make it home. It’s Friday night; time for a romantic dinner date with your beloved. It's a nice ending to a hectic week. Choose a romantic song to play while you make dinner together.
